# GitHub Style Markdown

Always use GitHub-style markdown formatting in [README.md](mdc:README.md) and other markdown files.

## GitHub Markdown Standards

### Headers
- Use `#` for main title (H1)
- Use `##` for major sections (H2)
- Use `###` for subsections (H3)
- Use `####` for sub-subsections (H4)
- Always include a space after the `#` symbols

### Lists
- Use `-` (hyphen) for unordered lists, not `*` or `+`
- Use `1.` for ordered lists
- Indent sub-items with 2 spaces
- Keep consistent spacing between list items

### Links
- Use `[Link Text](url)` format
- Make link text descriptive and meaningful
- Use relative links for internal references
- Include `.md` extension for markdown file links

### Emphasis
- Use `**bold**` for strong emphasis
- Use `*italic*` for light emphasis
- Use `***bold italic***` for combined emphasis
- Use `~~strikethrough~~` for deleted text

### Code
- Use `` `code` `` for inline code
- Use ``` ``` for code blocks
- Specify language after opening ``` when possible
- Indent code blocks with 4 spaces or use fenced blocks

### Tables
- Use `|` to separate columns
- Use `---` to separate header from content
- Align columns with `:---`, `:---:`, or `---:`
- Keep tables simple and readable

### Blockquotes
- Use `>` for blockquotes
- Use `>>` for nested blockquotes
- Include attribution when appropriate

### Horizontal Rules
- Use `---` for horizontal rules
- Place them between major sections

### Images
- Use `![Alt Text](image-url)` format
- Provide meaningful alt text
- Use relative paths for local images

